it's a great effort but sorry to say this is just a Taraana in Malhar; not really a Jam. 

For a real Jam in Malhar checkout Coke Studio Pakistan season 6 "Miyan ki Malhar"; that's a real Jam because it has bandishs from 3 different Gharanas(Patiala, Gwaliar & Bhopal) of North Indian/Pakistani Classical Music as well as musicianship from different part of the world.

snippet.textDisplay: Everyone has great things to say so I am not repeating them. But if there is one standout feature of Agam and Harishji it is that such is  perfection of discipline and precision coupled with outstanding talent that was evident in all their song compositions and ability for  fusion music that it did NOT need a Coke Studio to showcase it. All the same, glad that Coke Studio helped this highly underrated band get much needed exposure to people who haven't heard them.
